cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

This paper proposes a method for creating compact convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for vision tasks such as object classification, localization, and detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new network module that linearly combines sparse kernels, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper employs hand-crafted kernels with regular sparse patterns, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on various vision tasks, which could also place it under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
